column2: Which types of systems do you collect for?

column5: Do you collect systems you did not own/have easy access to before they were discontinued? (ex. collecting for SNES now despite never owning one as a child)
column6: Do you collect systems (currently being manufactured)?
column7: How likely are you to collect multiple variations (including special editions) of hardware?
column8: How often do you collect factory sealed games without the intention of opening them?
column9: Do you collect complete in box (CIB) games?
column10: Do you collect games with boxes/cases that are missing manuals or other inserts?
column12: When buying a used game that is confirmed functional, how likely is it that you would purchase a game with visible signs of wear (scratches, scuff marks, sun faded, etc.)?
column13: When buying a used game that is confirmed functional, how likely is it that you would purchase a game with a heavily damaged and illegible or missing label?
column14: How likely is price to influence your decision to purchase a sealed, CIB, case only, or loose game?
column15: Do you have a list of games you hope to own at some point in the future?
column16: Do you have a goal to collect every (retail) game for any of the systems you collect for?
column17: Do you have a goal to collect every game for a specific game series?
column18: Do you check a pricing guide (such as pricecharting.com) before purchasing a game?
column19: For older systems, how likely are you to purchase a game you have never played?
column20: How likely are professional/user reviews to influence your decision to purchase a game?
column21: How likely are you to purchase a game without looking up additional information if the price is affordable for your financial situation?
column22: When browsing a sale or shop which of these statements applies to your thought process?
column23: What age range do you fall in?
column26: What is the highest degree or level of school you have completed?
column27: What is your current employment status?
